1 A concurrent resolution recognizing the benefits of enhanced oil recovery and encouraging the
2 State of North Dakota and federal government to maintain favorable policies that support the
3 development of carbon capture technology and utilization of carbon dioxide as a commodity for
4 advancing energy security.
5 WHEREAS, the Bakken Formation is a world-class energy resource yielding 1.2 million
6 barrels of oil per day; and
7 WHEREAS, North Dakota's oil industry contributes approximately $8 million per day in
8 extraction and production tax revenues, $26 billion since 2008, and over half of total state tax
9 revenues annually; and
10 WHEREAS, oil and gas tax revenues contribute to the well-being of the state, providing a
11 stable tax base, prospering economy, well-paying jobs, and energy security; and
12 WHEREAS, current recovery methods produce only a small portion of the Bakken
13 Formation's estimated oil in place; and
14 WHEREAS, it is estimated that utilization of enhanced oil recovery methods could unlock
15 several billion barrels more of incremental oil production, and extend Bakken Formation
16 production by several decades; and
17 WHEREAS, North Dakota's coal industry supports nearly 12,000 jobs in the state,
18 contributes $2 billion in gross domestic product, and $100 million in state and local tax
19 revenues; and
20 WHEREAS, the coal industry has been a leader in pursuing technologies to capture carbon
21 dioxide from its coal-fired power and gasification facilities; and
22 WHEREAS, carbon dioxide captured from North Dakota's energy and agriculture facilities is
23 a valuable commodity that will be necessary to achieve full deployment of enhanced oil
24 recovery in North Dakota's oil shale formations and conventional reservoirs; and
