1 WHEREAS, the state has been a leader in investing in research and development to
2 unleash the full potential of all its energy resources, and in creating a regulatory environment
3 that fosters the development of carbon capture, utilization, and storage technologies; and
4 WHEREAS, successful deployment of enhanced oil recovery will unlock the full potential of
5 the Bakken Formation, enhance North Dakota's coal industry, and support the continued growth
6 of North Dakota's energy industries, supporting the Trump Administration's goals of achieving
7 energy dominance and energy security;
8 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
9 NORTH DAKOTA, THE SENATE CONCURRING THEREIN:
10 That the Sixty-ninth Legislative Assembly recognize the benefits of enhanced oil recovery
11 and encourage the State of North Dakota and federal government to maintain favorable policies
12 that support the development of carbon capture technology and utilization of carbon dioxide as
13 a commodity for advancing energy security; and
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the federal government is urged to develop policies that
15 encourage and incentivize utilization of carbon dioxide for enhanced oil recovery; and
16 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the federal government is urged to increase its
17 partnership with the State of North Dakota and its energy industries to advance carbon capture
18 technologies and enhanced oil recovery in the Bakken Formation; and
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State forward copies of this resolution
20 to the President of the United States, the Secretary of the Department of Energy, the Secretary
21 of the Department of the Interior, and each member of the North Dakota Congressional
22 Delegation.
